1
00:00:22,064 --> 00:00:23,983
<i>Are you already</i>
<i>a member of the Filipino group chat</i>

2
00:00:24,066 --> 00:00:24,984
<i>here in Morocco?</i>

3
00:00:25,067 --> 00:00:26,694
<i>It really helps in times of trouble.</i>

4
00:00:26,777 --> 00:00:28,612
<i>Some people approached me earlier.</i>

5
00:00:28,696 --> 00:00:31,741
<i>They snatched my passport,</i>
<i>and my dirhams were taken, too.</i>

6
00:00:31,824 --> 00:00:33,242
<i>Did you recognize who took it?</i>

7
00:00:33,325 --> 00:00:34,410
<i>No.</i>

8
00:00:34,493 --> 00:00:36,162
<i>Miss! Miss! Where's my money?</i>

9
00:00:36,454 --> 00:00:38,330
<i>Hello?</i>
<i>Your mother is in the hospital!</i>

10
00:00:38,414 --> 00:00:39,248
Are you Filipino?

11
00:00:39,331 --> 00:00:41,083
<i>My mom has stage four lung cancer.</i>

12
00:00:41,167 --> 00:00:43,461
<i>I promise... I'll return your money.</i>

13
00:00:43,544 --> 00:00:46,297
- You better return my money.
- Yana Kassir. That's my name.

14
00:00:46,380 --> 00:00:47,882
<i>I saw Mama.</i>

15
00:00:47,965 --> 00:00:50,468
- Tell her I don't care about her.
- <i>She's dead, Papa.</i>

16
00:00:51,051 --> 00:00:52,261
<i>The sheikh gave this to me.</i>

17
00:00:52,344 --> 00:00:54,680
<i>He said it's a Moroccan amethyst.</i>

18
00:00:54,764 --> 00:00:58,809
<i>A symbol of honor, truth, and love.</i>

19
00:01:08,068 --> 00:01:11,822
♪ <i>Love is never gone </i>♪

20
00:02:23,519 --> 00:02:24,645
Hey.

21
00:02:25,479 --> 00:02:26,981
Come back, okay?

22
00:02:29,275 --> 00:02:31,443
Of course I'll come back, Ma.

23
00:02:33,028 --> 00:02:34,321
I wrote to him.

24
00:02:35,739 --> 00:02:38,367
He said he's arriving today from Spain.

25
00:02:38,450 --> 00:02:39,535
We'll talk.

26
00:02:39,618 --> 00:02:41,161
Are you sure, Ma?

27
00:02:42,621 --> 00:02:44,164
Are you ready to face him?

28
00:02:44,874 --> 00:02:46,792
Do you think he'll forgive me?

29
00:02:51,005 --> 00:02:52,214
Or maybe...

30
00:02:53,549 --> 00:02:55,426
just ask for forgiveness for me.

31
00:02:56,510 --> 00:02:57,720
In case he doesn't make it in time--

32
00:02:57,803 --> 00:02:59,138
Ma!

33
00:02:59,221 --> 00:03:01,849
Don't say things like that!
You're so stubborn!

34
00:03:14,361 --> 00:03:15,863
I love you.

35
00:03:21,702 --> 00:03:23,704
I love you so much too, Ma.

36
00:03:37,801 --> 00:03:39,428
Teo, we'll go ahead, okay?

37
00:03:39,511 --> 00:03:40,596
Poy!

38
00:03:43,849 --> 00:03:45,851


39
00:03:55,903 --> 00:03:57,237
What took you so long?

40
00:03:58,197 --> 00:03:59,907
We've were calling you earlier.

41
00:03:59,990 --> 00:04:01,575
I had some things to take care of.

42
00:04:01,659 --> 00:04:03,786
So, is Diane ready?

43
00:04:04,370 --> 00:04:05,788
I'm here.

44
00:04:05,871 --> 00:04:07,039
Are we just going to move on?

45
00:04:08,374 --> 00:04:10,250
Do you even know
they've already taken down Safara?

46
00:04:11,043 --> 00:04:12,252
I know.

47
00:04:12,336 --> 00:04:15,589
That's exactly why I'm more nervous
about what we're about to do.

48
00:04:17,257 --> 00:04:19,426
Diane, what's with all this fear?

49
00:04:19,510 --> 00:04:22,179
There's no time for that.
Everything's already planned.

50
00:04:24,807 --> 00:04:28,978
No matter what happens,
we still meet at our spot at the Ruins.

51
00:04:32,106 --> 00:04:33,315
Okay.

52
00:04:34,775 --> 00:04:36,652
No matter what happens.

53
00:04:37,778 --> 00:04:38,612
Clear?

54
00:04:39,989 --> 00:04:41,699


55
00:04:50,374 --> 00:04:52,876


56
00:05:32,666 --> 00:05:35,210


57
00:05:58,817 --> 00:06:00,277
I'm in the room.

58
00:06:03,363 --> 00:06:04,239
Me, too.

59
00:06:09,620 --> 00:06:10,829
The sheikh is here.

60
00:06:12,372 --> 00:06:14,500


61
00:06:26,970 --> 00:06:27,971


62
00:06:28,472 --> 00:06:30,516

Good morning, sheikh and madam.

63
00:06:30,599 --> 00:06:34,186
Welcome. My name is Joseph,
and I'll be your butler for today.

64
00:06:34,269 --> 00:06:35,813
Where is Hakob, my butler?

65
00:06:36,855 --> 00:06:38,023
Excuse me, butler.

66
00:06:39,358 --> 00:06:40,567
A minute, please.

67
00:06:41,151 --> 00:06:42,861
- Peace be upon you.
Also with you.

68
00:06:43,445 --> 00:06:44,613


69
00:06:45,239 --> 00:06:47,783
The butler assigned to you
is on leave, sir.

70
00:06:47,866 --> 00:06:50,119
But don't worry, sir, it's just for today.

71
00:07:06,260 --> 00:07:07,094
Sheikh Jamal.

72
00:07:13,350 --> 00:07:14,351
They've entered the room.

73
00:07:16,979 --> 00:07:18,647
- Good morning.
Good morning.

74
00:07:19,857 --> 00:07:21,358
Chameleon.

75
00:07:21,441 --> 00:07:23,026

We are already in the parking.

76
00:07:24,486 --> 00:07:26,864
Get the money and
bring it to me as planned.

77
00:07:26,947 --> 00:07:28,240
<i>Yes, boss.</i>

78
00:07:38,250 --> 00:07:39,418
What's happened?

79
00:07:39,918 --> 00:07:41,128
May I, madam?

80
00:07:41,962 --> 00:07:43,964
- Don't worry, I will fix this right away.

81
00:07:44,882 --> 00:07:46,008


82
00:07:46,091 --> 00:07:48,385
- Call my bodyguard!
Okay, sir.

83
00:07:49,928 --> 00:07:52,723


84
00:07:56,727 --> 00:07:58,437
The sheikh wants to call you.

85
00:08:00,063 --> 00:08:01,023
What is this?

86
00:08:01,106 --> 00:08:03,150
- Call the manager.
Yes, sir.

87
00:08:05,819 --> 00:08:09,031


88
00:08:11,909 --> 00:08:14,036

Make sure this place is clean.

89
00:08:15,329 --> 00:08:17,497
Presidential Suite? Okay, right away, sir.

90
00:08:22,127 --> 00:08:24,379
Sheikh, the coordinator
called. You're needed in the event.

91
00:08:24,463 --> 00:08:25,923
Put the luggage in the cabinet.

92
00:08:28,008 --> 00:08:30,010


93
00:08:38,352 --> 00:08:39,519
You, out.

94
00:08:39,603 --> 00:08:41,521
- We'll call you when we need you.
- Okay, sir.

95
00:09:20,852 --> 00:09:21,770
Yana.

96
00:09:21,853 --> 00:09:24,356
<i>It's done, I got it. I'm heading out.</i>

97
00:09:39,246 --> 00:09:41,248
Gimo, maintenance is on the way!

98
00:09:57,180 --> 00:09:59,308
Excuse me.
Are you the butler?

99
00:09:59,391 --> 00:10:01,059
Can you open the room?

100
00:10:01,143 --> 00:10:02,269
I'm the maintenance.

101
00:10:11,320 --> 00:10:12,446
The TV, right?

102
00:10:20,245 --> 00:10:21,663
Did you plug it in?

103
00:10:29,629 --> 00:10:30,922
Please stay there.

104
00:10:32,758 --> 00:10:34,885
- Who let you in?
- The butler, sir.

105
00:10:35,927 --> 00:10:37,346
Where is the madam's phone?

106
00:10:37,429 --> 00:10:38,680
On the bed, sir.

107
00:10:48,565 --> 00:10:49,858
Where's the bag?

108
00:10:50,567 --> 00:10:52,152
- Huh?
- You stay there!

109
00:10:52,652 --> 00:10:53,862
Come back here!

110
00:10:56,114 --> 00:10:57,532
Hey, you!

111
00:10:57,616 --> 00:10:58,784
Sir, I don't know, sir!

112
00:10:58,867 --> 00:11:00,952
Sir! I don't know, sir!

113
00:11:03,455 --> 00:11:04,790
Where's the bag?

114
00:11:05,457 --> 00:11:06,792
I didn't see any bag, sir.

115
00:11:06,875 --> 00:11:08,835
- The bag was here!
- I don't know, sir.

116
00:11:08,919 --> 00:11:10,337
Tell me where is the bag!

117
00:11:49,376 --> 00:11:50,252
Sir!

118
00:11:52,170 --> 00:11:53,255
Someone, help!

119
00:12:00,595 --> 00:12:02,055
What happened, Gimo?

120
00:12:02,139 --> 00:12:04,266
The sheikh's bodyguard came back.

121
00:12:04,850 --> 00:12:06,226
He saw it was missing.

122
00:12:06,309 --> 00:12:08,895
That's why I got hit.

123
00:12:17,654 --> 00:12:18,655
Wait!

124
00:12:29,791 --> 00:12:31,251
Stay there for a while.

125
00:12:42,721 --> 00:12:44,139
Come on, come on!

126
00:13:07,913 --> 00:13:08,955
They're here!

127
00:13:09,039 --> 00:13:11,500
They're riding a delivery truck,
exiting the hotel.

128
00:13:12,417 --> 00:13:13,627
Go. Let's go.

129
00:13:16,546 --> 00:13:18,632
- Do you know him?
- No, sir.

130
00:13:18,715 --> 00:13:21,218
He just came in the room
and then he was looking for a bag.

131
00:13:21,301 --> 00:13:24,095
Yes, I saw that in the CCTV file.

132
00:13:24,179 --> 00:13:26,473
You were in the room
when this incident happened, right?

133
00:13:26,556 --> 00:13:28,808
Yes, sir. I was just fixing the... the TV.

134
00:13:28,892 --> 00:13:30,977
A pregnant woman
and a butler came in, too.

135
00:13:31,061 --> 00:13:32,687
- Do you know them?
- No, sir.

136
00:13:32,771 --> 00:13:34,189
Did you hear anything?

137
00:13:34,272 --> 00:13:36,566
- A name? A place?
- No, sir.

138
00:13:38,944 --> 00:13:40,362
You see the resemblance?

139
00:13:41,988 --> 00:13:43,532
Your co-worker, Jeffrey Alcala,

140
00:13:43,615 --> 00:13:46,368
told me that you
and this woman know each other.

141
00:13:46,451 --> 00:13:47,619
Is she your girlfriend?

142
00:13:48,787 --> 00:13:50,497
Are you connected with this group?

143
00:13:51,623 --> 00:13:54,167
No, no, sir. I don't know
anything about them.

144
00:13:58,129 --> 00:14:00,757
I guess we'll soon find out, Mr. Crisanto.

145
00:14:22,862 --> 00:14:23,989
Hello.

146
00:14:24,072 --> 00:14:26,199
- Hello.
- Is Yana here?

147
00:14:26,283 --> 00:14:29,077
- Yana? Who?
- Yana Kassir.

148
00:14:29,995 --> 00:14:31,246
Wait, wait.

149
00:14:31,621 --> 00:14:33,415
She's your delivery rider.

150
00:14:34,374 --> 00:14:36,334
No, she's not our delivery girl.

151
00:14:36,418 --> 00:14:38,086
She doesn't work here. Never.

152
00:14:38,670 --> 00:14:40,630
- Are you sure?
- Sorry, yes, I'm sure.

153
00:14:42,090 --> 00:14:43,216
Thank you.

154
00:14:46,303 --> 00:14:48,138
Gimo, get down from there!

155
00:14:48,221 --> 00:14:49,306
- Get down!
- Yana.

156
00:14:49,389 --> 00:14:51,182
- Come here. Come on!
- Leave me.

157
00:14:51,266 --> 00:14:53,143
- What are you saying?
- I'll stay here.

158
00:14:53,727 --> 00:14:55,520
You won't get your share!

159
00:14:55,604 --> 00:14:56,521
Do you want to end up with nothing?

160
00:14:56,605 --> 00:14:57,814
Come on!

161
00:14:58,148 --> 00:15:00,775
Yana, I have a request.

162
00:15:02,652 --> 00:15:05,822
Please send my share
to my family in Ilocos.

163
00:15:07,365 --> 00:15:10,327
So I can finally pay off my debts.

164
00:15:11,077 --> 00:15:14,289
So my sibling can finish school.

165
00:15:14,372 --> 00:15:15,582
It's up to you now.

166
00:15:18,835 --> 00:15:21,129
No, you'll be the one
to send it to your mother.

167
00:15:21,212 --> 00:15:22,505
Not me!

168
00:15:22,589 --> 00:15:23,673
We can get through this.

169
00:15:24,341 --> 00:15:26,134
Yana, I'll handle things here.

170
00:15:26,217 --> 00:15:27,469
Take the bags.

171
00:15:27,552 --> 00:15:30,305
It'll be hard to carry them
while helping Gimo. It'll slow us down.

172
00:15:30,889 --> 00:15:33,808
No matter what happens,
we meet at our spot at the Ruins.

173
00:15:35,810 --> 00:15:37,228
Go to your mother. Go!

174
00:15:37,312 --> 00:15:38,438
I'll come back for you.

175
00:15:38,521 --> 00:15:40,065
Stay strong, Gimo!

176
00:16:03,296 --> 00:16:05,215
Excuse me, I'm looking for Yana.

177
00:16:06,049 --> 00:16:07,676
Yes, who are you?

178
00:16:07,759 --> 00:16:09,219
I'm Teo Crisanto.

179
00:16:09,302 --> 00:16:10,512
I'm Yana.

180
00:16:11,012 --> 00:16:12,347
No, I meant Yana Kassir.

181
00:16:12,430 --> 00:16:13,973
Daughter of Nadia.

182
00:16:14,057 --> 00:16:15,642
Yes, I'm Yana Kassir.

183
00:16:16,142 --> 00:16:17,185
I'm her daughter.

184
00:16:17,769 --> 00:16:19,229
She's my mother.

185
00:16:19,312 --> 00:16:21,564
My mother, Nadia, passed away.

186
00:16:34,661 --> 00:16:36,371
I met a different Yana.

187
00:16:36,454 --> 00:16:37,497
Not you.

188
00:16:37,580 --> 00:16:40,625
You're probably referring to
the girl she's been living with.

189
00:16:40,709 --> 00:16:42,711
I've been living in Spain with my father

190
00:16:42,794 --> 00:16:44,212
after they separated.

191
00:16:44,295 --> 00:16:46,798
I don't know her name,
but she's been using mine.

192
00:16:47,382 --> 00:16:49,384
They all thought
she was her real daughter.

193
00:16:49,467 --> 00:16:51,845
But they're wrong. I'm her only daughter.

194
00:16:52,512 --> 00:16:53,930
She's a fake.

195
00:17:00,145 --> 00:17:01,354
Go.

196
00:17:24,544 --> 00:17:28,006
WHERE ARE YOU? YOUR MOTHER'S GONE.

197
00:17:56,785 --> 00:17:58,286
Where are
the things you stole?

198
00:17:58,369 --> 00:17:59,204
Let go of me!

199
00:17:59,287 --> 00:18:01,456
- Let go!
- Where are they, Diane?

200
00:18:01,539 --> 00:18:03,374
Listen, Khaled is on his way here.

201
00:18:03,458 --> 00:18:05,919
You might as well give me what you stole,

202
00:18:06,002 --> 00:18:07,420
I'll hide it, and we'll split it.

203
00:18:07,504 --> 00:18:09,172
You bastard!

204
00:18:09,255 --> 00:18:11,758
We worked hard for that! We earned that!

205
00:18:13,218 --> 00:18:14,219
What's that?

206
00:18:17,472 --> 00:18:19,766
Tell me where the stolen items are!

207
00:18:19,849 --> 00:18:22,685
When Boss Khaled gets here,
you'll get nothing!

208
00:18:24,103 --> 00:18:25,104
Where is it?

209
00:18:29,526 --> 00:18:30,693
Diane!

210
00:20:04,078 --> 00:20:05,455
Mama...

211
00:20:05,538 --> 00:20:06,956
Mama!

212
00:20:09,083 --> 00:20:10,168
Mama.

213
00:21:05,640 --> 00:21:09,102
Boss, I stopped them,
but Yana is not here.

214
00:21:14,357 --> 00:21:15,733
Where's Chameleon?

215
00:21:15,817 --> 00:21:18,027
I'm asking, where is she?

216
00:21:19,028 --> 00:21:20,279
I don't...

217
00:21:20,697 --> 00:21:22,281
I don't know!

218
00:21:25,660 --> 00:21:27,662
Boss, don't. No, no...

219
00:21:27,745 --> 00:21:29,122
Where is she?

220
00:21:33,793 --> 00:21:37,296
You are going to tell me. Where is she?

221
00:21:37,380 --> 00:21:38,923
I don't know!

222
00:21:45,471 --> 00:21:46,973
Your last chance.

223
00:21:47,265 --> 00:21:48,516
Tell me, where is she?

224
00:21:49,976 --> 00:21:51,310
Where is she?

225
00:21:51,978 --> 00:21:53,604
I don't know!

226
00:21:58,526 --> 00:21:59,527
Yana!

227
00:22:01,279 --> 00:22:02,405
- Yana!
- What?

228
00:22:02,488 --> 00:22:04,282
The cops have identified you.

229
00:22:04,365 --> 00:22:06,242
You're one of the three robbers
at the hotel.

230
00:22:08,703 --> 00:22:10,288
I thought you were just a pickpocket.

231
00:22:10,371 --> 00:22:11,414
Turns out you're a big-time thief.

232
00:22:11,497 --> 00:22:12,749
You don't know anything.

233
00:22:12,832 --> 00:22:15,501
Damn right! You made a fool out of me!

234
00:22:15,585 --> 00:22:17,045
Just be honest with me!

235
00:22:18,421 --> 00:22:20,006
Hold on, is Yana even your real name?

236
00:22:20,631 --> 00:22:22,633
I spoke to your mother's real daughter.

237
00:22:22,717 --> 00:22:24,635
If her name is Yana, then who are you?

238
00:22:26,095 --> 00:22:26,929
Tell me.

239
00:22:31,517 --> 00:22:33,144
I thought we built something nice.

240
00:22:34,604 --> 00:22:36,314
We trust each other because we're friends.

241
00:22:37,690 --> 00:22:39,025
We were happy, right?

242
00:22:40,234 --> 00:22:41,444
And now, what?

243
00:22:42,695 --> 00:22:44,322
Are you just a fraud?

244
00:22:46,240 --> 00:22:47,825
Yes, I'm a fraud, Teo.

245
00:22:49,535 --> 00:22:51,204
So, you were just fooling around?

246
00:22:53,372 --> 00:22:54,624
Tell me.

247
00:22:55,666 --> 00:22:56,876
Fooling around?

248
00:22:59,003 --> 00:23:02,173
You think all my feelings
for you weren't real?

249
00:23:03,674 --> 00:23:05,593
Tell me. Even the sex?

250
00:23:06,511 --> 00:23:08,304
I won't let you fool me anymore.

251
00:23:08,387 --> 00:23:11,057
You've caused so many problems.
You're a liar!

252
00:23:11,140 --> 00:23:13,059
Yes! I'm a liar.

253
00:23:13,810 --> 00:23:16,729
Pickpocket, thief...

254
00:23:17,355 --> 00:23:18,731
But just with other people!

255
00:23:19,315 --> 00:23:21,234
That won't work on me anymore.

256
00:23:22,235 --> 00:23:24,237
You can't just run away from your crimes.

257
00:23:24,320 --> 00:23:25,238
Just surrender!

258
00:23:30,243 --> 00:23:31,744
Do it then, if it pleases you.

259
00:23:33,663 --> 00:23:34,747
Yana!

260
00:23:50,555 --> 00:23:52,765
<i>Chameleon is at Semmarine Square.</i>

261
00:23:52,849 --> 00:23:54,183
Stop.

262
00:23:54,267 --> 00:23:55,810
They're at the square.

263
00:24:01,440 --> 00:24:02,650
Chameleon!

264
00:24:05,236 --> 00:24:06,362
Teo, run.

265
00:24:06,445 --> 00:24:08,114
Run!

266
00:24:08,197 --> 00:24:10,158
Stop! I have your friends!

267
00:24:18,457 --> 00:24:19,500
Wait, wait.

268
00:24:20,835 --> 00:24:21,669
Let's go.

269
00:24:55,203 --> 00:24:58,247
I got you.

270
00:24:59,874 --> 00:25:01,125
Freeze!

271
00:25:10,468 --> 00:25:11,886
Stop!

272
00:25:19,894 --> 00:25:21,270
Yana, please surrender!

273
00:25:21,938 --> 00:25:22,980
Put an end to this!

274
00:25:24,065 --> 00:25:25,274
Surrender to the cops.

275
00:25:38,704 --> 00:25:39,580
Teo!

276
00:25:48,339 --> 00:25:49,465
Yana!

277
00:26:05,523 --> 00:26:06,399
Yana!

278
00:26:42,852 --> 00:26:45,354
We inspected city surveillance footages.

279
00:26:45,730 --> 00:26:47,440
You were with Yana Kassir.

280
00:26:47,523 --> 00:26:49,317
You didn't contact us,

281
00:26:49,400 --> 00:26:51,152
knowing she's wanted.

282
00:26:51,235 --> 00:26:53,279
I don't even know where she was.

283
00:26:53,779 --> 00:26:55,448
The two of you
met in the morgue.

284
00:26:55,990 --> 00:26:58,576
How did that happen
without any communication?

285
00:26:59,327 --> 00:27:00,995
I took a chance at the morgue.

286
00:27:01,078 --> 00:27:03,372
Knowing how important
her dead mother was to her.

287
00:27:03,456 --> 00:27:04,915
It doesn't look like that.

288
00:27:05,541 --> 00:27:07,752
It looks like
you are running away together.

289
00:27:08,669 --> 00:27:10,796
You already know that she's wanted.

290
00:27:10,880 --> 00:27:12,590
And you chose to be with her.

291
00:27:12,673 --> 00:27:15,801
You make yourself a part
of all her crimes.

292
00:27:15,885 --> 00:27:17,762
No!

293
00:27:17,845 --> 00:27:18,846
That's not true.

294
00:27:18,929 --> 00:27:23,142
And that makes you an accessory
to all the crimes she committed.

295
00:27:24,518 --> 00:27:26,479
We got this from her bag.

296
00:27:27,480 --> 00:27:29,148
Lota Gracua.

297
00:27:29,231 --> 00:27:30,816
Spanish citizen.

298
00:27:33,194 --> 00:27:34,653
Lourdes Lapaz.

299
00:27:35,154 --> 00:27:36,280
Moroccan.

300
00:27:36,947 --> 00:27:38,199
I don't know any of them.

301
00:27:38,991 --> 00:27:40,868
Please, sir, you have to find Yana.

302
00:27:40,951 --> 00:27:42,286
Or whatever her name is.

303
00:27:42,370 --> 00:27:43,579
We did already.

304
00:27:43,662 --> 00:27:46,207
She was found dead in Sidi Kaouki.

305
00:28:46,934 --> 00:28:48,394
When I saw what happened to you

306
00:28:48,477 --> 00:28:49,979
in the Filipino group chat, Teo...

307
00:28:51,522 --> 00:28:53,065
I couldn't believe it.

308
00:28:54,608 --> 00:28:57,445
It is impossible that you'd
get involved in such a syndicate.

309
00:29:03,534 --> 00:29:08,205
Teo, I'm sorry
for everything that has happened.

310
00:29:10,583 --> 00:29:12,668
I can talk to Hassan

311
00:29:12,751 --> 00:29:14,170
because he probably
knows someone who can help--

312
00:29:14,253 --> 00:29:15,379
You don't have to.

313
00:29:22,511 --> 00:29:24,930
I can't just leave you here, Teo.

314
00:29:26,265 --> 00:29:28,809
I'll go to the embassy. I'll ask for help.

315
00:29:28,893 --> 00:29:29,977
I'll do the best I can.

316
00:29:30,060 --> 00:29:31,979
You know what?
I'll write a letter addressed

317
00:29:32,062 --> 00:29:34,148
to the ambassador and to our president.

318
00:29:34,231 --> 00:29:36,984
I'll do everything to get you out of here.

319
00:29:39,487 --> 00:29:41,655
I just want to talk to Papa and Issay.

320
00:29:49,079 --> 00:29:50,039
Hello, Pa.

321
00:29:54,376 --> 00:29:55,461
I'm sorry, Pa.

322
00:29:56,545 --> 00:29:58,881
Don't overthink it too much.

323
00:29:59,256 --> 00:30:02,343
What's important is that
Larajean is there for you.

324
00:30:02,718 --> 00:30:04,512
<i>Someone's helping you with your case.</i>

325
00:30:05,262 --> 00:30:09,183
I've been praying for you
day and night, Teo.

326
00:30:09,266 --> 00:30:11,602
Don't lose the bracelet I gave you.

327
00:30:18,025 --> 00:30:20,611
Pa, they only gave me
a few minutes for a call.

328
00:30:21,820 --> 00:30:23,280
We'll pray...

329
00:30:25,407 --> 00:30:27,493
that you get home safe soon.

330
00:30:27,576 --> 00:30:28,786
We love you so much.

331
00:30:29,787 --> 00:30:31,288
We will be waiting for you to come home.

332
00:30:32,414 --> 00:30:34,250
I love you and Issay so much, too.

333
00:31:07,116 --> 00:31:09,994
Hit him!

334
00:31:22,172 --> 00:31:23,674
Stop!

335
00:31:42,943 --> 00:31:44,236
Stop!

336
00:31:51,994 --> 00:31:52,911
Stand up.

337
00:32:00,836 --> 00:32:02,129
Stand up.

338
00:32:11,263 --> 00:32:13,057
<i>You have to know how to fight.</i>

339
00:32:14,767 --> 00:32:17,811
<i>But remember, this is not about</i>
<i>who is the strongest...</i>

340
00:32:17,895 --> 00:32:20,272
<i>...or who has the most strength.</i>

341
00:32:21,023 --> 00:32:24,693
<i>It's about knowing</i>
<i>how to outthink your opponents.</i>

342
00:32:24,777 --> 00:32:26,570
Let them think you are weak.

343
00:32:26,654 --> 00:32:28,113
Then when the time comes,

344
00:32:28,197 --> 00:32:30,115
you hit smarter, you hit harder.

345
00:32:35,996 --> 00:32:37,790
Anger is fire.

346
00:32:38,457 --> 00:32:40,501
<i>Wild, it burns everything.</i>

347
00:32:40,584 --> 00:32:42,336
<i>But with purpose...</i>

348
00:32:44,588 --> 00:32:46,507
<i>it becomes power.</i>

349
00:33:18,664 --> 00:33:22,668
Crisanto, you were detained following
an involvement in a criminal act.

350
00:33:22,751 --> 00:33:24,128
Several, in fact.

351
00:33:25,504 --> 00:33:29,216
However, there are moments
when justice softens its grip.

352
00:33:29,675 --> 00:33:31,719
Since your name was included
in a Royal Pardon

353
00:33:31,802 --> 00:33:33,804
signed and decreed by His Majesty...

354
00:33:36,598 --> 00:33:38,267
you are going to be freed today.

355
00:33:38,350 --> 00:33:39,893
Consider it an act of goodwill,

356
00:33:39,977 --> 00:33:41,562
diplomatic in its intention.

357
00:33:42,646 --> 00:33:44,064
That's why you're being released.

358
00:33:46,734 --> 00:33:47,818
Thank you, sir.

359
00:34:43,165 --> 00:34:44,541
I left the country with nothing.

360
00:34:49,546 --> 00:34:51,173
Now, I've come home, still with nothing.

361
00:35:29,044 --> 00:35:29,920
Teo.

362
00:35:34,800 --> 00:35:35,926
Are you okay?

363
00:35:36,802 --> 00:35:37,845
Let me get this.

364
00:35:38,053 --> 00:35:38,971
Issay!

365
00:35:41,223 --> 00:35:42,224
Issay!

366
00:35:42,307 --> 00:35:44,268
- Yes?
- Hurry! Pa!

367
00:35:44,351 --> 00:35:46,728
- What? What is it?
- Teo?

368
00:35:46,812 --> 00:35:48,313
Teo!

369
00:35:48,397 --> 00:35:49,398
My brother!

370
00:35:50,399 --> 00:35:51,775
You're finally here.

371
00:35:56,822 --> 00:35:58,240
Son?

372
00:36:06,623 --> 00:36:07,624
Uh...

373
00:36:14,047 --> 00:36:15,549
I'm sorry, Pa.

374
00:36:16,633 --> 00:36:17,843
Why are you saying sorry?

375
00:36:18,927 --> 00:36:22,055
I can still stand, walk, and work.

376
00:36:22,639 --> 00:36:24,892
What's important is you're finally home.

377
00:36:26,393 --> 00:36:28,270
No one can hurt you now. Come here.

378
00:36:48,332 --> 00:36:49,666
Thanks, Boss!

379
00:36:58,216 --> 00:37:00,427
Son, when my illness got worse,

380
00:37:01,845 --> 00:37:04,598
they had to amputate my foot.

381
00:37:06,516 --> 00:37:07,893
I was forced to sell the car repair shop.

382
00:37:08,685 --> 00:37:11,855
We didn't tell you
because I don't want you...

383
00:37:14,232 --> 00:37:15,108
to worry about it.

384
00:37:16,818 --> 00:37:18,904
This car wash business

385
00:37:20,447 --> 00:37:23,158
was built thanks to my gambling winnings.

386
00:37:25,619 --> 00:37:26,745
But the thing is,

387
00:37:27,496 --> 00:37:28,705
I don't win often.

388
00:37:28,789 --> 00:37:32,501
That's why Issay needed to quit school.

389
00:37:34,127 --> 00:37:36,129
I need to save up so she can go back.

390
00:37:38,340 --> 00:37:39,800
I'll look for a job, Pa.

391
00:37:40,968 --> 00:37:42,469
Issay will go back to school.

392
00:37:43,762 --> 00:37:45,681
And I'll buy you a prosthetic leg.

393
00:37:45,764 --> 00:37:49,267
Son, get settled first.

394
00:37:49,351 --> 00:37:51,144
And...

395
00:37:51,228 --> 00:37:54,189
forget about the bad things
that happened in Morocco.

396
00:37:56,525 --> 00:37:59,861
And helping us
shouldn't be your only dream.

397
00:37:59,945 --> 00:38:02,489
You should have dreams for yourself, too.

398
00:38:07,619 --> 00:38:08,620
Yes, Pa.

399
00:38:09,496 --> 00:38:10,831
I'll go back to school.

400
00:38:11,790 --> 00:38:13,709
It's not too late to make
our dreams happen, right?

401
00:38:15,711 --> 00:38:18,422
I hope my record in Morocco
won't be a problem.

402
00:38:18,505 --> 00:38:19,715
Don't worry, son.

403
00:38:20,882 --> 00:38:24,678
I know for sure you'll get a nice job.

404
00:38:25,679 --> 00:38:26,847
Have faith.

405
00:38:27,806 --> 00:38:30,934
I'll bet my right foot on that.

406
00:38:31,018 --> 00:38:32,102
Oh, Pa.

407
00:38:34,438 --> 00:38:36,148
Trust me, Pa. I'll fix this.

408
00:38:37,107 --> 00:38:38,275
I'll make it up to you.

409
00:39:25,238 --> 00:39:27,574
Teo! Teo!

410
00:39:27,657 --> 00:39:31,203
- Come in.
- Here's a copy of your resume.

411
00:39:31,995 --> 00:39:32,954
Here.

412
00:39:34,956 --> 00:39:35,874
Oh.

413
00:39:36,708 --> 00:39:38,376
Oh, wow!

414
00:39:38,460 --> 00:39:41,046
You look handsome.

415
00:39:41,129 --> 00:39:43,131
Are you trying to flirt with me?

416
00:39:45,175 --> 00:39:46,760
I told you not to.

417
00:39:46,843 --> 00:39:48,512
I'll work on it at a computer shop.

418
00:39:49,471 --> 00:39:50,806
But thanks for this.

419
00:39:52,015 --> 00:39:54,184
You talk as if we haven't
been friends for so long.

420
00:39:54,976 --> 00:39:58,271
You know I'll do everything to help you.

421
00:39:58,855 --> 00:40:01,024
Is there anything else I can do?

422
00:40:01,108 --> 00:40:02,859
Anything else I can help you with?

423
00:40:02,943 --> 00:40:04,194
No, this is all good.

424
00:40:04,277 --> 00:40:05,320
Thanks.

425
00:40:11,159 --> 00:40:12,119
Teo...

426
00:40:16,414 --> 00:40:19,501
Teo, have you forgiven me

427
00:40:19,584 --> 00:40:21,378
for what I did before?

428
00:40:24,381 --> 00:40:25,382
A long time ago.

429
00:40:26,591 --> 00:40:27,968
A really long time ago.

430
00:40:28,885 --> 00:40:32,013
A... about Hassan...

431
00:40:32,430 --> 00:40:34,641
- Hmm?
- We're done. It's over.

432
00:40:34,724 --> 00:40:36,101
I thought you loved him.

433
00:40:37,144 --> 00:40:38,979
I only told you that

434
00:40:39,646 --> 00:40:44,234
so... you'd forget about me.

435
00:40:45,735 --> 00:40:49,239
Screw that guy.
He was nothing but trouble.

436
00:40:51,616 --> 00:40:53,827
He didn't make me happy.

437
00:40:55,579 --> 00:40:56,705
Because...

438
00:40:57,414 --> 00:40:58,748
because the truth is

439
00:40:58,832 --> 00:41:00,375
I... I still love you.

440
00:41:01,751 --> 00:41:03,086
So, I left him.

441
00:41:03,170 --> 00:41:05,672
And I came back to the Philippines.

442
00:41:10,051 --> 00:41:14,556
Teo, now that you're free...

443
00:41:17,893 --> 00:41:22,105
Now that we're both single,

444
00:41:22,189 --> 00:41:24,941
what if we got back together?

445
00:41:27,527 --> 00:41:28,820
Larajean, a lot...

446
00:41:29,863 --> 00:41:31,406
a lot has changed.

447
00:41:33,283 --> 00:41:35,702
After everything I've been through...

448
00:41:37,204 --> 00:41:38,705
I'm done.

449
00:41:40,207 --> 00:41:42,083
Can we at least be friends?

450
00:41:47,714 --> 00:41:49,090
That's not a no.

451
00:41:49,758 --> 00:41:50,967
See?

452
00:41:51,468 --> 00:41:54,804
Fr... friends, okay?
Let's just be friends again.

453
00:41:55,513 --> 00:41:57,265
Okay?

454
00:41:59,392 --> 00:42:00,894
If you applied to me,

455
00:42:01,353 --> 00:42:02,354
I'd hire you immediately.

456
00:42:03,063 --> 00:42:05,774
Permanent,
with bonus, with benefits.

457
00:42:05,857 --> 00:42:07,108
On the spot.

458
00:43:03,873 --> 00:43:07,294
I can also repair cars
like Beetles and Mercedes.

459
00:43:07,377 --> 00:43:08,878
Engines are my forte.

460
00:43:08,962 --> 00:43:11,881
Carburetors, transmissions,
gas or diesel engines.

461
00:43:11,965 --> 00:43:14,175
I can identify anything,
even with my eyes closed.

462
00:43:14,259 --> 00:43:15,176
Really?

463
00:43:15,260 --> 00:43:16,678
It says in your resume

464
00:43:17,137 --> 00:43:18,805
that you worked as
maintenance staff in Morocco.

465
00:43:18,888 --> 00:43:21,308
It was the only job available.

466
00:43:21,391 --> 00:43:24,519
But I also fixed cars
on the side while I was there.

467
00:43:24,602 --> 00:43:26,521
We used to have a workshop.

468
00:43:26,604 --> 00:43:28,773
A mechanical and electrical repair shop.

469
00:43:29,232 --> 00:43:32,444
My father was also
a master automotive technician.

470
00:43:32,527 --> 00:43:34,070
I learned from him.

471
00:43:34,154 --> 00:43:35,572
I also took up a vocational course.

472
00:43:35,655 --> 00:43:36,948
Okay, all right.

473
00:43:37,032 --> 00:43:38,199
But you need to present me

474
00:43:38,283 --> 00:43:40,452
with an NBI or police clearance first.

475
00:43:42,871 --> 00:43:44,039
Okay, sir.

476
00:44:10,690 --> 00:44:13,610
Attorney, the media's already inside,
but the hearing hasn't started yet.

477
00:44:13,693 --> 00:44:15,320
We will have a pre-trial in ten minutes.

478
00:44:15,403 --> 00:44:16,613
The governor is in holding.

479
00:44:16,696 --> 00:44:18,073
The press would like a statement.

480
00:44:18,156 --> 00:44:19,491
I don't have a statement yet.

481
00:44:19,574 --> 00:44:20,617
Are our exhibits ready?

482
00:44:20,700 --> 00:44:21,785
Yes.
All queued and timestamped,

483
00:44:21,868 --> 00:44:23,036
USB and hard copy.

484
00:44:23,119 --> 00:44:24,579
Can I have a nail cutter, please?

485
00:44:25,413 --> 00:44:27,123
- Attorney?
- A nail cutter!

486
00:44:27,207 --> 00:44:28,958
You know the drill! Hurry up!

487
00:44:31,544 --> 00:44:32,712
Here, Attorney.

488
00:44:39,010 --> 00:44:40,011
Better.

489
00:44:40,637 --> 00:44:42,222
Now, let's get this over with.

490
00:44:44,224 --> 00:44:47,394
Mrs. Guevarra, did you give
Dale Gomez those sedatives

491
00:44:47,477 --> 00:44:48,520
on January 15th?

492
00:44:48,603 --> 00:44:51,189
According to Dale Gomez's
social media account,

493
00:44:51,272 --> 00:44:53,358
you invited him that day.

494
00:44:53,441 --> 00:44:55,652
But why did Enrico know his passwords?

495
00:44:55,735 --> 00:44:57,195
It proves the affair.

496
00:44:57,278 --> 00:44:58,696
I knew it!
They were having an affair!

497
00:44:58,780 --> 00:45:01,825
Whether there was an affair
or not, the question here is,

498
00:45:01,908 --> 00:45:03,368
did you kill Dale Gomez?

499
00:45:03,451 --> 00:45:05,120
The evidence shows
that you used the alleged affair

500
00:45:05,203 --> 00:45:08,123
to cover up the fact
that you poisoned Dale Gomez

501
00:45:08,206 --> 00:45:09,707
when he caught you stealing.

502
00:45:09,791 --> 00:45:12,377
I was about to drain you dry, Enrico!

503
00:45:12,460 --> 00:45:14,087
But your lover caught me!

504
00:45:14,170 --> 00:45:17,465
God forbid I let you be happy, Enrico!

505
00:45:17,549 --> 00:45:19,884
So, you killed him!
You killed Dale Gomez!

506
00:45:19,968 --> 00:45:21,010
He deserves it!

507
00:45:24,931 --> 00:45:26,182
Order in the court!

508
00:45:26,266 --> 00:45:27,684
No further questions.

509
00:45:43,658 --> 00:45:46,244
Sir, you have a record.

510
00:45:46,327 --> 00:45:48,872
Allegation
of physical assault.

511
00:45:48,955 --> 00:45:52,709
My father, who has
a disability, was being mocked.

512
00:45:52,792 --> 00:45:54,043
I just defended him.

513
00:45:54,127 --> 00:45:55,253
But the charges have been cleared.

514
00:45:55,336 --> 00:45:56,713
I was even able to work abroad.

515
00:45:56,796 --> 00:45:58,631
No warrant was issued.

516
00:45:58,715 --> 00:46:00,592
But in order to clear your record,

517
00:46:00,675 --> 00:46:03,970
you must obtain
a certified copy of the court dismissal

518
00:46:04,053 --> 00:46:06,097
and a clearance from the court.

519
00:46:06,181 --> 00:46:08,349
Bring the documents here,
and we'll update our system.

520
00:46:08,433 --> 00:46:09,684
I already had those before,

521
00:46:09,767 --> 00:46:11,644
but I gave them to my employer.

522
00:46:12,896 --> 00:46:15,190
Does that mean
I can't get a clearance now?

523
00:46:15,273 --> 00:46:17,233
I'm afraid so, sir.

524
00:46:17,317 --> 00:46:18,776
Not until we clear your record.

525
00:46:18,860 --> 00:46:23,114
So, you should start working
on getting those documents.

526
00:46:24,949 --> 00:46:26,034
- Thank you, sir.
- All right.

527
00:46:26,117 --> 00:46:27,285
Next, please!

528
00:46:27,368 --> 00:46:29,829
You have a meeting later
at 3:00 p.m. with Mr. Demetrio

529
00:46:29,913 --> 00:46:32,665
regarding the Cordero property situation.

530
00:46:32,749 --> 00:46:33,958
He'll present some documents.

531
00:46:34,042 --> 00:46:35,210
Thank you very much, Attorney.

532
00:46:35,293 --> 00:46:36,711
Anytime, Governor.

533
00:46:37,378 --> 00:46:39,255
- Thank you so much.
- I'll go ahead.

534
00:46:39,339 --> 00:46:42,217
He has updated documents
for your review.

535
00:46:42,300 --> 00:46:44,302
Cancel everything
I have scheduled after lunch, Eric.

536
00:46:44,385 --> 00:46:46,179
My wife's coming tomorrow.

537
00:46:48,806 --> 00:46:51,684
There's a last-minute check
for her birthday surprise.

538
00:46:51,768 --> 00:46:54,771
Attorney, if you want,
I can handle the party.

539
00:46:54,854 --> 00:46:56,314
So, it's one less thing
for you to worry about.

540
00:46:56,397 --> 00:46:57,774
It's okay. I want to do it.

541
00:46:57,857 --> 00:46:59,901
You know, when it comes
to Gem, I'm hands-on.

542
00:46:59,984 --> 00:47:02,487
Everything has to be perfect
for my perfect wife.

543
00:47:02,570 --> 00:47:06,199
Justice
for the people of Cordero!

544
00:47:06,282 --> 00:47:08,034
Give us back our land!

545
00:47:08,117 --> 00:47:09,327
- Justice!
- Justice!

546
00:47:09,410 --> 00:47:10,954
Justice for the people of Cordero!

547
00:47:11,037 --> 00:47:13,414
Give us back our land!

548
00:47:13,915 --> 00:47:14,832
Just email it to me, all right?

549
00:47:14,916 --> 00:47:15,792
And, Eric, please.

550
00:47:15,875 --> 00:47:18,378
Fix your collar. It's crooked.

551
00:47:18,461 --> 00:47:19,837
Noted, Attorney.

552
00:47:34,227 --> 00:47:35,603
Give us back our land!

553
00:47:47,991 --> 00:47:51,077
- Justice!
- Give us back our land!

554
00:49:02,398 --> 00:49:03,316
What the hell is your problem?

555
00:49:03,399 --> 00:49:05,610
- What is your problem?
- You bastard!

556
00:49:29,050 --> 00:49:30,134
You're hurt.

557
00:49:48,027 --> 00:49:50,488
Yes, the police report
has been filed, love.

558
00:49:51,406 --> 00:49:53,032
Nobody wanted
for this to happen.

559
00:49:54,242 --> 00:49:55,993
Yes, the police are
already looking for the bastards

560
00:49:56,077 --> 00:49:58,121
after investigating
the place of the incident.

561
00:50:00,123 --> 00:50:02,083
Don't worry,
I'm fine now, love.

562
00:50:03,084 --> 00:50:04,544
No, the stab wound
isn't fatal.

563
00:50:06,003 --> 00:50:08,339
You'll see when you arrive here tomorrow.

564
00:50:08,423 --> 00:50:10,550
I'm still strong
as a stallion.

565
00:50:11,968 --> 00:50:13,094
Does that sound good?

566
00:50:17,473 --> 00:50:18,349
Love, wait.

567
00:50:18,433 --> 00:50:19,726
I'll see you later. Love you.

568
00:50:23,980 --> 00:50:25,148
Hello, Pa?

569
00:50:27,108 --> 00:50:28,735
No, nothing serious.

570
00:50:29,193 --> 00:50:31,446
But if I hadn't gotten help right away,

571
00:50:31,529 --> 00:50:33,448
things would've probably been worse.

572
00:50:34,365 --> 00:50:35,283
Yeah, yeah.

573
00:50:35,366 --> 00:50:36,701
I'll see you later, Pa.

574
00:50:37,160 --> 00:50:38,202
Bye.

575
00:50:45,001 --> 00:50:46,836
Thank goodness you're finally awake.

576
00:50:48,045 --> 00:50:49,505
The tests were completed.

577
00:50:50,381 --> 00:50:53,176
The doctor said, uh,
it's a mild brain trauma injury.

578
00:50:53,259 --> 00:50:54,927
But you have nothing to worry about.

579
00:50:55,928 --> 00:50:56,846
Also, the doctor said

580
00:50:56,929 --> 00:50:58,389
you'll have to stay here
for the next few days

581
00:50:58,473 --> 00:50:59,682
for observation.

582
00:50:59,766 --> 00:51:02,226
Oh, no, sir, I don't have
the money to pay for all of this.

583
00:51:02,310 --> 00:51:03,936
Everything's taken care of.

584
00:51:05,938 --> 00:51:07,190
Thank you for saving my life.

585
00:51:08,232 --> 00:51:09,984
I owe my life to you.

586
00:51:11,778 --> 00:51:14,363
Anybody would've done the same thing.

587
00:51:14,447 --> 00:51:16,824
That, I have to disagree with.

588
00:51:17,742 --> 00:51:19,660
Everybody's in it
for themselves these days.

589
00:51:20,536 --> 00:51:21,954
Survival of the fittest,

590
00:51:22,246 --> 00:51:24,081
the strongest, the safest.

591
00:51:24,999 --> 00:51:26,501
No one really cares about anyone.

592
00:51:26,584 --> 00:51:28,461
But when there's gossip,
they suddenly show up.

593
00:51:29,629 --> 00:51:30,963
I don't mean to generalize, but...

594
00:51:31,631 --> 00:51:32,590
almost everyone.

595
00:51:33,591 --> 00:51:35,176
What made you say that?

596
00:51:35,259 --> 00:51:36,844
I see it every day.

597
00:51:37,637 --> 00:51:39,138
In the cases I've handled.

598
00:51:40,556 --> 00:51:41,808
By the way,

599
00:51:42,683 --> 00:51:44,435
Attorney Ace Verona.

600
00:51:45,019 --> 00:51:46,312
Oh.

601
00:51:46,395 --> 00:51:48,022
No, it's okay.

602
00:51:50,900 --> 00:51:52,610
Mateo Crisanto.

603
00:51:53,194 --> 00:51:54,403
Teo, for short.

604
00:51:55,988 --> 00:51:58,908
When you're fully recovered, contact me.

605
00:51:59,575 --> 00:52:01,202
There's a job offer waiting for you.

606
00:52:01,994 --> 00:52:02,995
Really, sir?

607
00:52:03,538 --> 00:52:05,373
That's great, I've been looking for work.

608
00:52:05,957 --> 00:52:06,916
What can you do?

609
00:52:06,999 --> 00:52:08,292
I know how to do mechanic work.

610
00:52:08,376 --> 00:52:10,753
I could also be a driver.
Anything you need.

611
00:52:10,837 --> 00:52:12,713
Perfect. A mechanic.

612
00:52:12,797 --> 00:52:14,590
Give me a call, okay?

613
00:52:14,674 --> 00:52:15,675
Here.

614
00:52:21,013 --> 00:52:23,558
Actually, there will be
a birthday party at home soon.

615
00:52:23,641 --> 00:52:26,060
It would be my honor
to introduce you to my family.

616
00:52:26,853 --> 00:52:27,770
You'll be there, okay?

617
00:52:46,873 --> 00:52:48,708
- Do you need anything?
- Uh...

618
00:52:48,791 --> 00:52:51,836
Boss, Attorney Ace Verona invited me.

619
00:52:51,919 --> 00:52:54,171
- Do you have an invitation?
- Is it necessary?

620
00:52:54,255 --> 00:52:56,215
No invitation, no entry.

621
00:52:56,299 --> 00:52:57,884
That's a directive from the higher-ups.

622
00:52:58,134 --> 00:52:59,760
Hang on. I know him.

623
00:52:59,844 --> 00:53:02,388
He rescued Sir Ace
when things got rough on the road.

624
00:53:02,471 --> 00:53:03,639
He's invited.

625
00:53:04,181 --> 00:53:05,391
Are you sure?

626
00:53:05,474 --> 00:53:06,726
I don't want to get in trouble.

627
00:53:06,809 --> 00:53:10,313
You'll be in way more trouble
if you don't let him in.

628
00:53:10,396 --> 00:53:12,607
All right, sir. Come, follow me.

629
00:53:43,220 --> 00:53:44,388
Thank you, boss.

630
00:53:50,144 --> 00:53:51,312
Good evening.

631
00:53:55,775 --> 00:53:56,817
Hi.

632
00:53:58,486 --> 00:53:59,779
Ma! Pa!

633
00:54:00,404 --> 00:54:01,948
- My dear.
- Wow.

634
00:54:02,531 --> 00:54:04,450
- Hello, my princess.
- Look at you.

635
00:54:04,533 --> 00:54:06,243
My beautiful daughter.

636
00:54:06,327 --> 00:54:07,536
- Hi, Pa.
- Hi.

637
00:54:07,620 --> 00:54:09,080
What is this you're wearing?

638
00:54:09,163 --> 00:54:11,290
Where are the jewels
that I told you to wear?

639
00:54:11,374 --> 00:54:14,418
Ma, I'm comfortable in this.

640
00:54:14,502 --> 00:54:15,461
Besides,

641
00:54:15,544 --> 00:54:16,921
it feels too ostentatious.

642
00:54:17,004 --> 00:54:18,506
It's not even my birthday.

643
00:54:18,589 --> 00:54:20,383
- But, you know--
- Let her be.

644
00:54:20,466 --> 00:54:22,176
Let's just enjoy the party.

645
00:54:23,260 --> 00:54:25,388
Raya, next time, just follow, okay?

646
00:54:25,471 --> 00:54:26,973
Yes, Your Honor.

647
00:54:27,348 --> 00:54:29,016
Pa. I mean, Pa.

648
00:54:30,309 --> 00:54:31,394
Let's go.

649
00:54:35,606 --> 00:54:36,440
Ace!

650
00:54:36,524 --> 00:54:38,025
- Raya!
- Hi.

651
00:54:38,109 --> 00:54:39,568
- Oh, hi. Nice to see you.
- How are you?

652
00:54:39,652 --> 00:54:40,611
- Wow!
- Pa.

653
00:54:40,695 --> 00:54:43,489
- Looking very dapper, my son.
- Thank you, Ma.

654
00:54:43,572 --> 00:54:45,324
- You're looking great, too.
- Thank you.

655
00:54:45,408 --> 00:54:46,450
- Good, good.
- Oh, wait.

656
00:54:46,534 --> 00:54:47,910
- Nice to see you.
- I'll just say hi.

657
00:54:48,494 --> 00:54:49,453
Teo!

658
00:54:50,037 --> 00:54:51,122
- Teo!
- Boss!

659
00:54:51,706 --> 00:54:52,623
Glad you could make it.

660
00:54:52,707 --> 00:54:54,083
Thank you for inviting me.

661
00:54:54,166 --> 00:54:55,292
Thank you so much for coming.

662
00:54:56,293 --> 00:54:57,712
You've got a big house.

663
00:54:59,213 --> 00:55:00,297
I appreciate you coming.

664
00:55:00,381 --> 00:55:01,465
- Enjoy.
- Thank you!

665
00:55:01,549 --> 00:55:02,466
Thanks, sir.

666
00:55:06,846 --> 00:55:09,015
Ace! She's here!

667
00:55:09,098 --> 00:55:10,766
- Excuse me.
- Sure thing, boss.

668
00:55:15,688 --> 00:55:16,647
Excuse me!

669
00:55:16,981 --> 00:55:20,192
Ladies and gentlemen,
my beautiful wife, Gem,

670
00:55:20,276 --> 00:55:22,361
who is celebrating her birthday tonight.

671
00:55:23,029 --> 00:55:24,613
Happy birthday to Gem!

672
00:55:24,697 --> 00:55:26,365
Happy birthday! Happy birthday!

673
00:55:26,449 --> 00:55:27,491
Cheers, everybody!

674
00:55:47,970 --> 00:55:48,888
Thank you.

675
00:55:48,971 --> 00:55:50,139
Thank you for coming.

676
00:55:50,222 --> 00:55:51,515
Thank you so much for coming.

677
00:55:51,599 --> 00:55:52,475
Enjoy the rest of the night, okay?

678
00:55:52,558 --> 00:55:54,310
- Happy birthday.
- Thank you.

679
00:55:58,981 --> 00:56:00,524
- Are you okay?
- Mm-hmm.

680
00:56:01,025 --> 00:56:02,610
- Happy birthday.
- Thank you.

681
00:56:02,693 --> 00:56:04,070
- Bro, thank you for coming.
- I like your dress!

682
00:56:04,153 --> 00:56:05,446
It's nice to see you.

683
00:56:13,746 --> 00:56:15,998
- How many glasses have you had?
- Three?

684
00:56:17,750 --> 00:56:19,210
Uh, love, I'm getting a bit hungry.

685
00:56:19,293 --> 00:56:20,461
Can you get me some...

686
00:56:20,544 --> 00:56:21,754
crackers and cheese?

687
00:56:22,338 --> 00:56:24,381
I'll also get you some cold cuts.

688
00:56:24,965 --> 00:56:25,966
Thank you, love.

689
00:56:34,809 --> 00:56:35,935
Thank you.

690
00:56:40,606 --> 00:56:41,649
I'd also like some, please.

691
00:56:56,163 --> 00:56:57,206
Yana.

692
00:57:02,795 --> 00:57:04,088
Yana Kassir.

693
00:57:12,054 --> 00:57:13,222
Excuse me?

694
00:57:15,641 --> 00:57:16,934
Yana Kassir.

695
00:57:18,686 --> 00:57:19,937
Yana who?

696
00:57:21,480 --> 00:57:23,274
I think you have the wrong person.

697
00:57:34,410 --> 00:57:36,036
<i>That woman is now my wife.</i>

698
00:57:36,120 --> 00:57:37,955
You just forced me
to accept her into our family.

699
00:57:38,038 --> 00:57:39,290
You're my family.

700
00:57:39,373 --> 00:57:41,667
Family is family,
even if we are not perfect.

701
00:57:41,750 --> 00:57:44,086
<i>I am perfect, and so are my children.</i>

702
00:57:45,129 --> 00:57:46,297
Relax, relax!

703
00:57:46,380 --> 00:57:48,007
If you don't follow my rules,

704
00:57:48,090 --> 00:57:49,133
you're fired.

705
00:57:49,216 --> 00:57:50,801
<i>What other proof</i>
<i>do you want, Teo?</i>

706
00:57:50,885 --> 00:57:52,803
<i>The police found Yana's body.</i>

707
00:57:52,887 --> 00:57:54,096
<i>We just saw each other, Pa.</i>
<i>She's alive.</i>

708
00:57:54,180 --> 00:57:56,682
Maybe you should look for another job.

709
00:57:56,765 --> 00:57:58,726
Once a poison, always a poison.

710
00:57:58,809 --> 00:58:00,227
She won't ruin
my life again.

711
00:58:00,311 --> 00:58:02,271
<i>I'll see to it that her life</i>
<i>gets destroyed.</i>
